text: Seriously people, this is a movie that says and I quote "Submitting is ducking so God can hit your husband." and more than some random words sputtered by an utterly forgettable character that quote actually sums up one of the movies major themes. And let me tell you, of all the pieces of entertainment I've ever watched this has probably the worst relationship advice ever. In fact, I'm actually worried someone sees this and thinks this is exactly how they should behave.   In a real, healthy relationship no one should submit to anyone, both partners should be completely equal and communication should never be an issue, much less something one of the spouses is afraid of. If your partner does something that hurts, bothers or belittles you, then the best thing you can do is to talk to him or her about it. If you try to be reseonable and just start a normal, calm conversation and they simply end up making a fight out everything, even if it's easily the most sensible of complaints, then you're not the problem, they are. You didn't do anything wrong, they did. And please, please don't excuse such behaviors by saying "he is a man, they don't like being nagged by their wives" because that just ridiculous. Men are definitely not a bunch of rabid wild dogs ready to lash out at the tiniest of provocations, they are just as capable of being rational and of having reasonable conversations as women are.   If you really want to save your relationship, talk with your significant other, if things are really bad go see a marriage counselor. And if you don't want to be in that relationship anymore, there's no shame in asking for a divorce. And if your spouse abuses you physically or otherwise, please go seek help, go to the police or a shelter or just talk to a friend. Acting like a freaking doormat to your husband will hardly make things better in any of these situations.   And if you do believe in the power of prayer that's great. And if you decide to clear out your closet and use it to pray instead that's a fine too, I actually think it makes more sense to have a whole room to pray in than a whole room to put your clothes in (in my country people use wardrobes and that's enough). But remember that God can't do everything for you. If you pray to win the lottery you still have to go buy a ticket, if you pray to save your relationship you still have work on it, you can't just expect things to miraculously fall on your lap.
